reviews.text: Changed ownership multiple times but it keeps the same style of cuisine, retain some prior waitresses, and possibly some chef behind the scene. Serves quick and dirty lunch set that comes with tea, rice, main dish, and free soup or soy milk on the house,  AND pretty delicious delicacy during dinner time.
Great food and reasonable prices

Ate here on a Friday night, tried the fried beef in wraps/pancakes which was really nice, and the Dan dan noodles. The Dan dan noodles were a tad bland as I left them too long to eat, once the flavour was mixed in well they were very enjoyable. Not much English from the staff but polite and helpful and the menu is in English with clear photos or descriptions. Decor is a tad old, but overall a pleasant meal.
Shanghainese food. Some dishes good, some average.
Seen a chef or a worker swore (using foul language) at a Filipino maid just in front of the shop in City Garden when they shut their gate just after their opening hour.
